### [Proverbs Chapter 3](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 3:1](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">pro 3:1</span></span>

The study of truth commended. God must be feared, honored, and trusted,
and filial submission, under chastisement, exhibited. The excellence of
wisdom urged and illustrated by its place in the divine counsels. Piety
enforced by a contrast of the destiny of the righteous and the wicked.
(Pro. 3:1-35)

law \[and\] commandments--all divine instructions (see on [Psa
119:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa119.htm#001.md) and [Psa
119:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa119.htm#004).md).

let thine heart keep--or sincerely observe ([Pro
4:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro004.htm#013.md); [Pro
5:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro005.htm#002).md).

[Proverbs 3:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 3:2</span></span>

length . . . life--often promised as blessings ([Psa
21:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa021.htm#004.md); [Psa
91:16](../../../bib/kjv/psa091.htm#016).md).

peace--includes prosperity ([Psa
125:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa125.htm#005).md).

add--abound to thee.

[Proverbs 3:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#003.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_003">pro 3:3</span></span>

mercy and truth--God's faithfulness to His promises is often expressed
by these terms ([Psa 25:10](../../../bib/kjv/psa025.htm#010.md); [Psa
57:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa057.htm#003).md). As attributes of men, they
express integrity in a wide sense ([Pro
16:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#006.md); [Pro
20:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro020.htm#028).md).

bind . . . write . . . heart--outwardly adorn and inwardly govern
motives.

[Proverbs 3:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 3:4</span></span>

favour--grace, amiability ([Pro 22:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro022.htm#011.md);
[Psa 45:2](../../../bib/kjv/psa045.htm#002).md); united with this,

a good understanding--(Compare Margin), a discrimination, which secures
success.

in the sight . . . man--such as God and man approve.

[Proverbs 3:5](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">pro 3:5</span></span>

Trust . . . heart--This is the center and marrow of true wisdom ([Pro
22:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro022.htm#019.md); [Pro
28:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro028.htm#025).md). The positive duty has its
corresponding negation in the admonition against self-confidence.

[Proverbs 3:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">pro 3:6</span></span>

ways-- ([Psa 1:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa001.htm#001).md).

acknowledge--by seeking His wise aid ([Pro
16:3](../../../bib/kjv/pro016.htm#003.md); [Psa
37:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#005.md); [Jer
9:23-24](../../../bib/kjv/jer009.htm#023).md).

direct--literally, "make plain" (compare [Heb
12:13](../../../bib/kjv/heb012.htm#013).md).

[Proverbs 3:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">pro 3:7</span></span>

(Compare [Pro 27:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro027.htm#002.md); [Rom
12:16](../../../bib/kjv/rom012.htm#016).md).

fear . . . evil--reverentially regarding His law.

[Proverbs 3:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 3:8</span></span>

It--This conduct.

health--(Compare Margin).

to thy navel--for all the organs of nourishment.

marrow--(Compare Margin).

bones--frame of body. True piety promotes bodily health.

[Proverbs 3:9](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">pro 3:9</span></span>

(Compare [Pro 11:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro011.htm#025.md); [Exo
23:19](../../../bib/kjv/exo023.htm#019.md); [Deu
18:4](../../../bib/kjv/deu018.htm#004.md); [Isa
32:8](../../../bib/kjv/isa032.htm#008.md); [Co2
9:13](../../../bib/kjv/co2009.htm#013).md).

[Proverbs 3:10](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#010.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_010">pro 3:10</span></span>

presses--or wine fats ([Joe 2:24](../../../bib/kjv/joe002.htm#024.md); [Joe
3:13](../../../bib/kjv/joe003.htm#013).md).

[Proverbs 3:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">pro 3:11</span></span>

The true intent of afflictions considered; they do not contradict the
assertion of the blessed state of the pious ([Job
5:17](../../../bib/kjv/job005.htm#017.md); [Heb
12:5-6](../../../bib/kjv/heb012.htm#005).md).

[Proverbs 3:12](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#012.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_012">pro 3:12</span></span>

he delighteth--or receiveth as denoting reconciliation regarding the
offense which produced chastisement.

[Proverbs 3:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#013.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_013">pro 3:13</span></span>

findeth--literally, "reaches," or "obtains by seeking."

getteth--literally, "draws out," as metals by digging.

[Proverbs 3:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 3:14</span></span>

The figure of [Pro 3:13](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#013.md) carried out.

it--that is, wisdom.

merchandise of silver--acquisition by trading.

fine gold--dug gold, solid as a nugget.

[Proverbs 3:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">pro 3:15</span></span>

rubies--gems, or pearls.

[Proverbs 3:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 3:16</span></span>

Wisdom personified as bringing the best blessings (compare [Mat
6:33](../../../bib/kjv/mat006.htm#033.md); [Ti1
4:8](../../../bib/kjv/ti1004.htm#008).md).

[Proverbs 3:17](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#017.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_017">pro 3:17</span></span>

Her ways--such as she directs us to take.

[Proverbs 3:18](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#018.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_018">pro 3:18</span></span>

Wisdom allegorized as

a tree of life-- ([Gen 2:9](../../../bib/kjv/gen002.htm#009.md); [Gen
3:22](../../../bib/kjv/gen003.htm#022).md) whose fruit preserves life,
gives all that makes living a blessing.

[Proverbs 3:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">pro 3:19</span></span>

The place of wisdom in the economy of creation and providence commends
it to men, who, in proportion to their finite powers, may possess this
invaluable attribute, and are thus encouraged by the divine example of
its use to seek its possession.

[Proverbs 3:21](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#021.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_021">pro 3:21</span></span>

sound wisdom--(compare [Pro 2:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro002.htm#007).md).

let . . . eyes--that is, these words of instruction.

[Proverbs 3:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 3:22</span></span>

assign reasons in their value for happiness and ornament, guidance and
support in dangers, both when waking and sleeping.

[Proverbs 3:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">pro 3:25</span></span>

Be not--or, "You shall not be."

sudden fear--what causes it ([Pro
1:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#027).md), any unlooked-for evil ([Psa
46:3](../../../bib/kjv/psa046.htm#003.md); [Psa
91:12](../../../bib/kjv/psa091.htm#012.md); [Pe1
3:14](../../../bib/kjv/pe1003.htm#014).md).

desolation-- ([Pro 1:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro001.htm#027).md).

[Proverbs 3:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 3:26</span></span>

The reason; such as are objects of God's favor.

be thy confidence--literally, "in thy confidence," in the source of thy
strength (compare [Nah 3:9](../../../bib/kjv/nah003.htm#009.md), for the
same construction, Hebrew).

[Proverbs 3:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">pro 3:27</span></span>

Promptly fulfil all obligations both of justice and charity (compare
[Jam 2:15-16](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#015).md).

[Proverbs 3:29](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#029.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_029">pro 3:29</span></span>

Do not abuse confidence and avoid litigation.

[Proverbs 3:31](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">pro 3:31</span></span>

oppressor--or man of mischief. The destiny of successful evildoers warns
against desiring their lot ([Psa
37:1-2](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#001.md), [Psa
37:35-36](../../../bib/kjv/psa037.htm#035).md).

[Proverbs 3:32](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#032.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_032">pro 3:32</span></span>

Reasons for the warning.

froward-- ([Pro 2:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro002.htm#015).md).

secret . . . righteous--in their communion ([Amo
3:7](../../../bib/kjv/amo003.htm#007).md).

[Proverbs 3:33](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#033.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_033">pro 3:33</span></span>

curse . . . wicked--It abides with them, and will be manifested.

[Proverbs 3:34](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#034.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_034">pro 3:34</span></span>

The retribution of sinners, as in [Psa
18:26](../../../bib/kjv/psa018.htm#026.md).

[Proverbs 3:35](../../../bib/kjv/pro003.htm#035.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_035">pro 3:35</span></span>

inherit--as a portion.

shame--or disgrace, as opposed to honor.

promotion--(Compare Margin); as honor for well-doing makes men
conspicuous, so fools are signalized by disgrace.

